<p>IRN 3/2014 
<b>Iran (Islamic 
Republic of) 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Arbitrary 
detention;  
Freedom of 
expression;  Iran;   
</b> 
</p>
<p>Alleged forced closure of the newspaper Aseman and the arrest of information 
technology activists. According to the information received, on 21 February 2014, 
Tehran media court closed the reformist daily Aseman (Sky) for publishing an article 
on 18 February 2014, in which a university lecturer criticized qisas (retribution in 
kind) punishment. On 3 December 2013, authorities also arrested 16 Information 
Technology activists in Kerman, including Messrs&#8217; Aliasghar Honarmand, Abbas 
Vahedi, Hossein Nozari, Reza Nozari, Amir Sadeghpour, Mehdi Faryabi, Ehsan 
Paknejad and Ms. Malieh Nakhei. Of the 16 persons arrested, seven worked for the 
tech website Narenji.ir and were accused of being in contact with enemy media. Since 
their arrest, the detainees have been kept in solitary confinement, have had no access 
to a lawyer and have been subjected to psychological pressure.  
</p>
<p>05/06/2014 
 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
