<p>Alleged restrictions on the right to freedom of expression and opinion in the context 
of political debate and electoral processes in Turkey. According to the information 
received, on 20 March 2014, authorities blocked access to microblogging through 
Twitter and threatened to block access to other social media sites and Youtube, 
allegedly due to the publication of information criticizing the Government, in the 
context of Municipal elections which took place on 30 March. Reportedly, despite a 
temporary injunction decision on 26 March by an administrative court in Ankara 
ordering the telecommunication authorities to restore access to Twitter, the website 
remained blocked. It is also alleged that national legislation, namely Law No. 5651 
(2007) and Law 6518 (2014), imposes undue restrictions to internet access and the 
right to freedom of expression and opinion. 
