<p>OTH 3/2014 
<b>Other 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Indigenous 
peoples;   
</b> 
</p>
<p>Concerns over the pejorative connotations of the mascot of the Washington Redskins 
football team. According to the information received, the term &#8220;redskins&#8221; is a hurtful 
reminder for many of the long history of mistreatment of Native American people in 
the United States of America. The term &#8220;redskin&#8221; for many is inextricably linked to a 
history of suffering and dispossession, and should be understood to be a pejorative 
and disparaging term that fails to respect and honour the historical and cultural legacy 
of the Native Americans in the United States. 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
