<p>IDN 1/2014 
<b>Indonesia 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of 
expression;  
Freedom of 
peaceful assembly 
and of association;  
Human rights 
defenders;   
</b></p>
<p>Alleged undue restrictions on the exercise of the rights to freedom of peaceful 
assembly, expression and association of members of the Indigenous People of Biafra 
(IPB) based in Indonesia. According to the information received, IPB members based 
in Indonesia intend to hold a peaceful rally on 30 May 2014 to honour the memory of 
the millions of Biafrans killed during the Biafra-Nigeria war. However, they were not 
able to obtain permission from the authorities to hold the rally because IPB members 
are foreign nationals. The authorities informed them that permission could be granted 
if IPB was registered as an organization under domestic legislation. However, IPB 
members&#8217; previous attempts to register the organization were unsuccessful.  
</p>
