charges of &#8220;trafficking in persons&#8221;. Mr. Tillaev was previously sentenced to 
administrative detention on 20 September 2013 and released on 5 October 2013. 
While in detention, Mr. Tillaev was reportedly tortured. On 2 January 2014, Mr. 
Tillaev was arrested on the basis of an allegedly invalid arrest warrant. Grave concern 
is expressed at the severity of this sentence, the reports of torture while in detention, 
and the alleged lack of due process. Mr. Tillaev is a founding member of the Union of 
Independent Trade Unions, which works in support of labour migrants.  
