<p>Alleged death threats against a lawyer and killing of his client for denouncing 
corruption within the police. According to information received, Mr. Wesley Pereira 
Fuganti, a lawyer, and his client Mr. X, were threatened by police officers after 
denouncing corruption involving the police in the city of Salto, S&#227;o Paulo. On 29 
November 2012, Mr. X was allegedly killed by a former police officer. After this 
event, Mr. Fuganti requested protection from the Brazilian authorities without success. 
Mr. Fuganti left with his family for the United Kingdom where their application for 
asylum was reportedly denied on 27 February 2014. 
