<p>Alleged incommunicado detention of bloggers and freelance journalists who have 
been advocating for a space for free public dialogue, freedom of expression and 
access to information in Ethiopia. According to the information received, six members 
of the blogging collective Zone Nine, Messrs&#8217; Befeqadu Hailu, Atnaf Berahane, 
Zelalem Kiberet, Natnael Feleke and Abel Wabela, and Ms. Mahlet Fantahun, and 
three freelance journalists, Messrs&#8217; Tesfalem Waldyes and Asemamaw Haile Giorgis, 
and Ms. Edom Kasaye, are being held incommunicado at the Maikelawi detention 
centre since 25 and 26 April 2014. They reportedly appeared at Arada first instance 
court on Sunday 27 April 2014 and are scheduled to appear before the court on 7 and 
8 May 2014 on charges of working with foreign human rights organizations and 
inciting violence through social media to create instability in the country. 
