<p>Alleged incommunicado detention of the founding president of the Saudi Civil and 
Political Rights Association (ACPRA). According to the information received, Dr. 
Abdulrahman Al-Hamed, human rights defender and founding president of ACPRA, 
signed a statement on 12 April 2014 calling for the trial of the Minister of Interior for 
suppressing public freedoms. On 17 April 2014, Dr. Al-Hamed was detained while 
reporting to the Criminal Investigation Department in Burayda. While in detention, he 
has not been allowed to see his family or his lawyer. Members of ACPRA were the 
subject of three earlier communications sent on 3 February 2014, see A/HRC/24/21, 
case no. SAU 1/2014, on 27 March 2013, see A/HRC/24/21, case no. SAU 5/2013, 
and on 21 December 2012, see A/HRC/23/51, case no. SAU 13/2012. 
