<p>OTH 5/2014 
<b>Other 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Adequate 
housing;  Extreme 
poverty;  Freedom 
of peaceful 
assembly and of 
association;  
Health;  Water 
and Sanitation;   
</b> 
</p>
<p>Follow-up letter concerning alleged forced eviction of residents living in 
Jagatsinghpur District, Odisha, India and surrounding areas. According to the 
information received, up to 20, 000 people may be forced to leave their homes as a 
result of land being acquired for the construction of an integrated steel plant and a 
captive port by Korean steel corporation, Pohang Iron and Steel Corporation 
(POSCO). Reports suggest that the construction of the steel plant will result in serious 
violations of the human rights of affected people, including the right to an adequate 
standard of living, right to food, right to adequate housing, right to water and 
sanitation, right to health, right to education, and other related rights of people living 
in extreme poverty.  Reports further indicate that the rights of those opposing the 
project have been suppressed resulting in a series of human rights abuses. 
</p>
<p>25/07/2014 
 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
