<p>Alleged limitations on access to justice for migrant farmworkers in fourteen states of the 
U.S.A. According to information received, lack of legislation and implementation of 
existing legislation enables the detrimental nation-wide practice of denying or not 
allowing certain human rights defenders, in particular legal advocates and other 
community service providers, meaningful access to migrant farmworker in labour camps, 
including by allegedly harassing and threatening these human rights advocates.  
