<p>USA 13/2013 
<b>United States of 
America 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Torture;   
</b> 
</p>
<p>Alleged excessive use and practices of prolonged solitary confinement, poor conditions 
of detention and retaliatory measures. According to the information received, from 8 
July 2013, hundreds of prisoners in the California Department of Corrections and 
Rehabilitation have been conducting a hunger strike in protest of being placed in solitary 
confinement and denied certain basic necessities. Allegedly, the protest is in response to 
inaction by prison officials after a negotiated agreement after a 20-day hunger strike in 
July 2011. The prisoners are protesting against being subjected to solitary confinement 
for over 22 hours a day, some prisoners have been enduring isolation for decades, with 
inadequate food rations and quality, and overly restrictive policies regarding hobby 
materials and family visits. Reportedly, there are concerns regarding retaliation against 
the strikers, by further restricting family visits and denying any opportunity to contact 
family over the phone. Reportedly, there are also threats being made by the Corrections 
Secretary to obtain a court order to begin force feeding the prisoners.  
</p>
<p>18/07/2014 
 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
